  "prompt": "Where are Samsung phones made?",
  "response": "Samsung phones are primarily manufactured in several countries, including:\n\n1. South Korea - Samsung's home country, where some high-end models are produced\n2. Vietnam - A major production hub for Samsung, where many smartphones are made\n3. India - Samsung has significant manufacturing facilities in the country\n4. China - Some models were previously produced here, though production has decreased\n5. Brazil - Samsung has a manufacturing plant for some models in Brazil\n\nThe specific manufacturing location can vary depending on the model and current production strategies. Vietnam has become especially important for Samsung's smartphone production in recent years.",
